ReferenceDocuments.name: Is pre-study hemoglobin great
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 9 g/dl?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 1
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 9 g/dl OR greater than or equal to 5.6 mmol/L?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 2
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 8 g/dl?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 4
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 90 g/L (or 9 g/dl)?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 3
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 10 g/dl?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 5
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than 9 g/dL?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 6
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 8 g/dL?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 7
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 9 g/dL?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 9
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 9.0 g/dL?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 10
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 10 g/dl and patient has not had blood transfusions in the 28 days prior to entry/randomization?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 11
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 10 g/dL with no blood transfusion in the past 28 days?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 17
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 8 g/dl, within 2 weeks of randomization?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 8

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 13
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 10 g/dl within 4 weeks prior to administration of study treatment  and patient has not had blood transfusions (packed red blood cells and platetet transfusions) in the past 28 days?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 12
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 9 g/dl without transfusion for at least 7 days prior to screening?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 14
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 8 g/dL within 2 weeks of the initiation of treatment?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 16
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 9 g/dl (patients may be transfused to this level)?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 15
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than 10 g/dl within 4 weeks prior to administration of study treatment  and patient has not had blood transfusions (packed red blood cells and platelet transfusions) in the past 28 days?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 18
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 10 g/dl within 28 days prior to administration of study treatment  and patient has not had blood transfusions (packed red blood cells and platelet transfusions) in the past 28 days?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 20
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 9 g/dl for mono-therapy?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 19
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 10 g/dl with no blood transfusion  within 28 days prior to administration of therapy?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 21
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 9 g/dL or if anemia is related to bone marrow involvement with lymphoma is hemoglobin greater than or equal to 8 g/dL?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 22
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 8 g/dl, within 7 days before starting treatment?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 23
ReferenceDocuments.description: If patient has been assigned to receive Veliparib, is hemoglobin greater than or equal to 10.0 g/dL and patient has had no blood transfusions in the past 28 days?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 25
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 8 g/d, unless there is documented bone marrow involvement by lymphoma?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 27
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is screening visit hemoglobin greater than or equal to 8 g/dL?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 26

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 24
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 8 g/dL (within 14 days of enrollment)?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 28
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than 8 g/dL?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 29
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 10.0 g/dL and patient has had no blood transfusions in the past 28 days?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 32
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 10 g/dL with no packed red blood cell transfusion in the 14 days prior to starting therapy?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex -30
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 80 g/L (or 8 g/dl)?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 31
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 10 g/dL with no blood transfusions within the past 28 days?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 33
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 10 g/dL (within 7 days of study drug initiation) with no blood transfusion in the past 28 days?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 35
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 9 g/dL (greater than or equal to 8.0 g/dL for gastric cancer [GC] only), within 8 days of enrollment?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 34

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 36
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin 8 g/dl?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 38
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 9 g/dL or 5.6 mmol/L without transfusion or erythropoietin dependency (within 7 days of assessment)?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 37
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 9.5 g/dL and transfusion independent (defined as not requiring more than 2 units of red blood cell (RBC) transfusions during the 4-week period prior to screening)?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 39
ReferenceDocuments.description: Does patient have pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 10 g/dl within 14 days of randomization/enrollment?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 40
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 9 g/dl independent of transfusion, within 14 days prior to enrollment?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 41
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 8 g/dL or greater than or equal to 5.6 mmol/L?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 42
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 9.0 g/dL (greater than or equal to 8.0 g/dL for gastric cancer [GC] only) within 14 days of enrollment and no transfusions with red blood cells or platelets within 1 week prior to screening assessment?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 43
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 9 g/dL within 2 weeks of enrollment with no blood transfusion in the past 4 weeks?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 44
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 9 g/dL or 5.6 mmol/L?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 45
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 9 g/dl (stable for 2 weeks without transfusion or erythropoiesis-stimulating agent), within 14 days prior to study registration?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 46
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 9 g/dl OR greater than or equal to 5.6 mmol/L, without packed red blood cell (pRBC) transfusion within the prior 2 weeks?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 47
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 10 g/dL, blood transfusion to reach desired level must be at least 14 days prior to enrollment?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 48
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than 5.0 mmol/L (greater than 8.0 g/dL)?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 49
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 9 g/dL (patients may be transfused to achieve this value)?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 50
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is pre-study hemoglobin greater than or equal to 9 g/dl OR greater than or equal to 5.6 mmol/L, without packed red blood cell (pRBC) transfusion within the prior 14 days of registration?
